💼 Ratio Comparison Dashboard

Welcome to the Ratio Comparison Dashboard project! This dashboard provides a detailed comparison of financial ratios across multiple real estate companies, helping users evaluate financial performance, operational efficiency, liquidity, profitability, and capital structure.

📋 Project Overview

This project leverages Power BI to analyze and compare the financial health of leading real estate companies using key financial ratios and performance indicators. The dashboard enables stakeholders, investors, and analysts to identify strengths, weaknesses, and overall business stability through interactive visualizations.

🚀 Features
Liquidity Analysis: Evaluate short-term financial stability using Current Ratio and Quick Ratio.
Profitability Analysis: Compare ROA, ROE, ROCE, Gross Profit Margin, Operating Margin, and Net Profit Margin.
Efficiency Analysis: Measure asset utilization and working capital efficiency through turnover ratios.
Leverage Analysis: Assess debt management using Debt-Equity Ratio, DSCR, and Interest Coverage Ratio.
Capital Structure Insights: Visualize the balance between equity, reserves, and liabilities.
Comparative Company Analysis: Benchmark financial performance across multiple companies.
🛠️ Technologies Used
Power BI: Interactive dashboard creation and data visualization.
Financial Data Analysis: Ratio analysis and comparative business evaluation.
Data Modeling: Structured datasets for financial reporting and insights.
📂 Dashboard Highlights

The dashboard focuses on delivering actionable insights by answering questions such as:

Which company has the strongest liquidity position?
Which business generates the highest profitability and returns?
How efficiently are companies managing assets and receivables?
Are companies relying more on equity or debt financing?
Which company demonstrates the best overall financial health?
📊 Analysis Highlights

Key business insights identified from the dashboard include:

Arkade Developers demonstrates strong overall financial performance with high profitability and excellent debt servicing capability.
MICL maintains the strongest liquidity position and inventory efficiency.
Marathon Nextgen Realty leads in operating and net profit margins.
Suraj Estate Developers shows stable and balanced financial performance.
Integrated Spaces Limited performs well in receivables management but has weaker liquidity compared to peers.
📈 Business Value

This dashboard helps:

Investors evaluate company performance and financial stability.
Management identify operational strengths and improvement areas.
Analysts compare industry players using standardized financial metrics.
Stakeholders make data-driven strategic and investment decisions.
